verses.text_plain: A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet upon Shigionoth.
verses.verse_html:
1A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet upon Shigionoth. ▼
▼ upon…: or, according to variable songs, or, tunes, called in Hebrew, Shigionoth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ upon…: or, according to variable songs, or, tunes, called in Hebrew, Shigionoth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ upon…: or, according to variable songs, or, tunes, called in Hebrew, Shigionoth

verses.text_plain: O Lord, I have heard thy speech, and was afraid: O Lord, revive thy work in the midst of the years, in the midst of the years make known; in wrath remember mercy.
verses.verse_html:
2O Lord, I have heard thy speech, and was afraid: O Lord, revive thy work in the midst of the years, in the midst of the years make known; in wrath remember mercy. ▼
▼ speech: Heb. report, or, hearing
 , ▼
▼ revive: or, preserve alive

footnotes.body_html: ▼ speech: Heb. report, or, hearing
▼ revive: or, preserve alive

verses.text_plain: God came from Teman, and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory covered the heavens, and the earth was full of his praise.
verses.verse_html:
3God came from Teman, and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory covered the heavens, and the earth was full of his praise. ▼
▼ Teman: or, the south

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Teman: or, the south

verses.text_plain: And his brightness was as the light; he had horns coming out of his hand: and there was the hiding of his power.
verses.verse_html:
4And his brightness was as the light; he had horns coming out of his hand: and there was the hiding of his power. ▼
▼ horns…: or, bright beams out of his side

footnotes.body_text: ▼ horns…: or, bright beams out of his side
footnotes.body_html: ▼ horns…: or, bright beams out of his side

verses.text_plain: Before him went the pestilence, and burning coals went forth at his feet.
verses.verse_html:
5Before him went the pestilence, and burning coals went forth at his feet. ▼
▼ coals: or, diseases

verses.text_plain: He stood, and measured the earth: he beheld, and drove asunder the nations; and the everlasting mountains were scattered, the perpetual hills did bow: his ways are everlasting.
verses.verse_html: 6He stood, and measured the earth: he beheld, and drove asunder the nations; and the everlasting mountains were scattered, the perpetual hills did bow: his ways are everlasting.

verses.text_plain: I saw the tents of Cushan in affliction: and the curtains of the land of Midian did tremble.
verses.verse_html:
7I saw the tents of Cushan in affliction: and the curtains of the land of Midian did tremble. ▼
▼ Cushan: or, Ethiopia
 , ▼
▼ in…: or, under affliction, or, vanity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in…: or, under affliction, or, vanity
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: or, under affliction, or, vanity

verses.text_plain: Was the Lord displeased against the rivers? was thine anger against the rivers? was thy wrath against the sea, that thou didst ride upon thine horses and thy chariots of salvation?
verses.verse_html:
8Was the Lord displeased against the rivers? was thine anger against the rivers? was thy wrath against the sea, that thou didst ride upon thine horses and thy chariots of salvation? ▼
▼ of…: or, were salvation?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: or, were salvation?

verses.text_plain: Thy bow was made quite naked, according to the oaths of the tribes, even thy word. Selah. Thou didst cleave the earth with rivers.
verses.verse_html:
9Thy bow was made quite naked, according to the oaths of the tribes, even thy word. Selah. Thou didst cleave the earth with rivers. ▼
▼ earth…: or, rivers of the earth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ earth…: or, rivers of the earth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ earth…: or, rivers of the earth

verses.text_plain: The mountains saw thee, and they trembled: the overflowing of the water passed by: the deep uttered his voice, and lifted up his hands on high.
verses.verse_html: 10The mountains saw thee, and they trembled: the overflowing of the water passed by: the deep uttered his voice, and lifted up his hands on high.

verses.text_plain: The sun and moon stood still in their habitation: at the light of thine arrows they went, and at the shining of thy glittering spear.
verses.verse_html:
11The sun and moon stood still in their habitation: at the light of thine arrows they went, and at the shining of thy glittering spear. ▼
▼ at the light…: or, thine arrows walked in the light

footnotes.body_text: ▼ at the light…: or, thine arrows walked in the light
footnotes.body_html: ▼ at the light…: or, thine arrows walked in the light

verses.text_plain: Thou didst march through the land in indignation, thou didst thresh the heathen in anger.
verses.verse_html: 12Thou didst march through the land in indignation, thou didst thresh the heathen in anger.

verses.text_plain: Thou wentest forth for the salvation of thy people, even for salvation with thine anointed; thou woundedst the head out of the house of the wicked, by discovering the foundation unto the neck. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
13Thou wentest forth for the salvation of thy people, even for salvation with thine anointed; thou woundedst the head out of the house of the wicked, by discovering the foundation unto the neck. Selah. ▼
▼ by…: Heb. making naked

footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: Heb. making naked

verses.text_plain: Thou didst strike through with his staves the head of his villages: they came out as a whirlwind to scatter me: their rejoicing was as to devour the poor secretly.
verses.verse_html:
14Thou didst strike through with his staves the head of his villages: they came out as a whirlwind to scatter me: their rejoicing was as to devour the poor secretly. ▼
▼ came…: Heb. were tempestuous

tokens.text: they came out as a whirlwind

footnotes.body_html: ▼ came…: Heb. were tempestuous

verses.text_plain: Thou didst walk through the sea with thine horses, through the heap of great waters.
verses.verse_html:
15Thou didst walk through the sea with thine horses, through the heap of great waters. ▼
▼ heap: or, mud

verses.text_plain: When I heard, my belly trembled; my lips quivered at the voice: rottenness entered into my bones, and I trembled in myself, that I might rest in the day of trouble: when he cometh up unto the people, he will invade them with his troops.
verses.verse_html:
16When I heard, my belly trembled; my lips quivered at the voice: rottenness entered into my bones, and I trembled in myself, that I might rest in the day of trouble: when he cometh up unto the people, he will invade them with his troops. ▼
▼ invade…: or, cut them in pieces

tokens.text: in myself, that I might rest
he will invade them with his troops

footnotes.body_text: ▼ invade…: or, cut them in pieces
footnotes.body_html: ▼ invade…: or, cut them in pieces

verses.text_plain: Although the fig tree shall not blossom, neither shall fruit be in the vines; the labour of the olive shall fail, and the fields shall yield no meat; the flock shall be cut off from the fold, and there shall be no herd in the stalls:
verses.verse_html:
17Although the fig tree shall not blossom, neither shall fruit be in the vines; the labour of the olive shall fail, and the fields shall yield no meat; the flock shall be cut off from the fold, and there shall be no herd in the stalls: ▼
▼ fail: Heb. lie

verses.text_plain: Yet I will rejoice in the Lord, I will joy in the God of my salvation.
verses.verse_html: 18Yet I will rejoice in the Lord, I will joy in the God of my salvation.

verses.text_plain: The Lord God is my strength, and he will make my feet like hinds’ feet, and he will make me to walk upon mine high places. To the chief singer on my stringed instruments.
verses.verse_html:
19The Lord God is my strength, and he will make my feet like hinds’ feet, and he will make me to walk upon mine high places. To the chief singer on my stringed instruments. ▼
▼ chief…: or, overseer
 , ▼
▼ stringed…: Heb. Neginoth

tokens.text: and he will make me to walk
